# WFMA Project

QGIS project for Wimmera region flood analysis.

## Key Files

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `wfma.qgs` | Main QGIS project file |
| `scripts/` | Standalone Python scripts (run with `python-qgis`) |
| `scripts/qmls/` | QML layer styles |
| `configs/` | Server configs (nginx, qgis-server) |

## Layers

- **Properties**: Property parcels vector layer
- **LGA**: Local Government Area boundaries (8 features)
- **Depth**: Parent group for flood depth rasters

## Data Structure

- Source mirror: `C:\Users\m.rahman\qgis\pozi_mirror\data\flood\`
- Local depth data: `data\depth\{area}\*.tif`
- All depth rasters use CRS EPSG:7854

## Layer Group Structure

```
Depth/
  └── {Area}/
        └── *.tif (raster layers)
```

## Running Scripts

```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\QGIS 3.44.3\bin\python-qgis.bat" <script.py>
```

## Scripts Reference

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `import_depths.py` | Import TIFFs into "Depth" group |
| `remove.py` | Clear all layers under "Depth" |
| `select.py` | Toggle layer visibility |
| `select.py -none` | Deselect all |
| `select.py -a <name>` | Select by area name |
| `initiate.py` | Copy data from source mirror |
